column2: Hi Dave! I'm new to the Project Management Industry. I noticed on the Pmi website that we have to show documents about past projects and training. What counts as a project I've led?
column5:
Any project where you were leading and directing project activities would qualify. Depending on your education background, you would need a minimum of three to five years of project management experience to qualify for the certification exam.

PMI defines a project as “a temporary endeavor undertaken to create a unique product, service or result”. If your experience is related to operationsal activities, it would not count. Operationsal activities are ongoing and permanent with a repetitive output.

Here is an article that outlines the difference between operational and project activities that you may find helpful.

https://www.pmchamp.com/3-things-you-need-to-know-about-projects-and-operations/

column2: Hello Dave! What kind of documentation is needed to present past projects and training on the pmi.org website?
column5: The online application includes templates for entering each project that you worked on. You simply need to fill in each field with the appropriate information for each project that you worked on. You do not need to provide proof or additional documentation with your application. You would only need to supply additional documentation if your application is chosen for an audit. In that case, PMI will provide you with details on what inforamtion is required to complete the audit.

column2: test 2
Hi, how can I get access to the learner kit to apply for the exam?
column5:
Please note that you only need the Learner Kit if you plan to use this bootcamp to meet the 35 contact hours of project management education on your PMP application.

Your organization’s training staff or HR Department should be helping to facilitate the purchase of the Learner Kit by contacting your company's Skillsoft Account Executive. The Learner Kit is not available through your learning portal. For more information about the kit, I recommend checking out the video in the PMP Learner Kit Information Video found in the Watch tab of the Project Management Professional (PMP) ATP Bootcamp: 8 Day NA Cohort channel in Percipio or from our GitHub site. 

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP8Day

column2: Hi, how can I get access to the learner kit to apply for the exam?
column5:
If there is no process setup for them and they are asking you to purchase it on your own, you can start the purchase of the Learning kit from this web site by clicking on the Buy button.  You will be redirected to another page to make the purchase.

https://www.skillsoft.com/pmp-voucher-offering

The e-commerce price is $119, reflecting PMI’s pricing for the content and the additional e-commerce processing charges and tax. It may take a few days to receive the email with the access key with instructions on how to claim your Learner Kit.

Note 1: The e-commerce price is subject to change.

Note 2: The access key will be emailed to you from donotreply@imarc.com. Please be sure to check your Junk or Spam folders. If you don't receive the email with your access key after a few days please contact Customer Support.

https://support.skillsoft.com/contact.asp

Access Keys must be redeemed within 12 months of purchase. Once redeemed, your materials are available for 12 months. Access Keys can only be redeemed once.
